frameDefinitions: These words relate to the relative ordering of two events or times.
An Event begins at a certain Time and Place.
The Agent is assigned to a Post where he or she performs a task associated with that Post.
An Event continues at a certain Place through Time.
An object Theme moves in the direction of a Goal.
A Process comes to an end.
frameExamples: <t>After</t> she arrived , she laid out her papers on the desk.
Pyongyang agreed to suspend its withdrawal while talks <t>continued</t> with Washington.
Some students <t>arrived</t> at the school on Sunday.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is the event which is  being located in time with respect to some other event: The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is profiled, in contrast to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>, which is backgrounded.
The <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen> is the event  with respect to which the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is located.
The <fen>Focal_participant</fen> is the participant in the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> which is profiled as being in a relation of relative time to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>.
Name of the <fen>Event</fen> which occurs.
When the <fen>Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Event</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to a <fen>Post</fen> to perform a task involving a <fen>Salient_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Post</fen> is a location or station assigned to the <fen>Agent</fen> where a task or tasks are to be performed.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is centrally involved in the task the <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to perform. It is normally located at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> works at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> staffs the <fen>Post</fen>.
Name of the <fen>Event</fen> which is continuing.
When the <fen>Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Event</fen> takes place.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the object that moves. It may be an entity that moves under its own power, but it need not be.
<fen>Goal</fen> is any expression that tells where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up, or would end up, as a result of the motion.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arriving event occurs.
Name of the event which occurs.
When the event ends.
Where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Hours of eating and drinking</fex> followed the wedding ceremony.
Hours of eating and drinking followed <fex>the wedding ceremony</fex>.
Sue was staffing <fex>the entrance</fex> when everything started to go wrong.
Working the front desk <fex>at a real estate office</fex> is not as fulfilling as it might seem.
